  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulator.header": "Storing energy via accumulators",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulator.text_1": "An accumulator can be used to store electrical energy",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulator.text_2": "Charge it with a voltage of 24V",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulator.text_3": "Simply connect the positive to the positive and negative to the negative",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulator.text_4": "The accumulator will start charging",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulator.text_5": "After it's charged, it can power other components",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulators_series.header": "Connecting accumulators in series",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulators_series.text_1": "Accumulators can be connected in series to increase their voltage",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulators_series.text_2": "Each accumulator feeds into the next",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.accumulators_series.text_3": "This battery pack contains 10 batteries at 24V, charge it with 240V",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.alternator.header": "Setting up an alternator",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.alternator.text_1": "Alternators can be used to convert rotational force to electricity",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.alternator.text_2": "Surround the rotors with stators",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.alternator.text_3": "The alternator will start inducing a voltage.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.alternator.text_4": "184V",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.alternator.text_5": "Use a Transformer to fine-tune the voltage.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.alternator.text_6": "You might want to use a Voltage Regulator to regulate the voltage even further.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.header": "An intuitive approach to understanding electricity",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_1": "Imagine a wire connected in a loop.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_10": "In this case, this movement heats up the bulb's filament, the heat makes it glow.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_11": "Notice how the number of incoming dots is equal to the number of outgoing dots.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_12": "This is the definition of Kirchhoff's Current Law.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_2": "Little dots are placed on this wire. Think of them as electrons.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_3": "Its like a chain. These dots can move, but they can't move away from each other.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_4": "Voltage sources try to move this chain. They try to pull from one side, and push to the other.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_5": "Notice how the number of these dots stay constant. These dots don't represent energy themselves, their movement is energy.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_6": "This is actually a short circuit.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_7": "There is no resistance, and the voltage source is able to move these dots really fast!",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_8": "Connect it through a device instead.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.basics.text_9": "Devices use the movement of these dots as energy.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.bulb_mob_spawning.header": "Bulbs & mob spawning",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.bulb_mob_spawning.text_1": "Bulbs will prevent mob spawning",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.bulb_mob_spawning.text_2": "Even when they are off",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.connectors.header": "Connecting Wires",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.connectors.text_1": "Connectors and Wires can be used to relay electricity.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.connectors.text_2": "To remove existing wires, use an empty spool.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.connectors.text_3": "Insulated wires can be dyed.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.connectors.text_4": "Nodes can be labeled with a name tag.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.connectors.text_5": "The node's label will be displayed when hovering over it with a wire spool.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.connectors_chunks.header": "Wires through unloaded Chunks",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.connectors_chunks.text_1": "Electricity stays functional outside of loaded chunks.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.header": "Using current transformers",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_1": "Sometimes, it may be difficult to measure the amperage of a circuit",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_10": "Never open-circuit a current transformer!",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_11": "The current transformer tries to replicate the current from the top to the bottom, but it can't, because the bottom circuit is not complete!",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_12": "As a result, almost no current flows, and the bottom voltage rises to extremely high values!",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_2": "An ammeter here would be inaccessible",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_3": "A current transformer can 'relay' current",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_4": "Connect an ammeter to the bottom connectors",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_5": "Connect the top part in series to the measured wire",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_6": "The ammeter will display the measured current",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_7": "The current from the top of the current transformer ...",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_8": "... will be mirrored on the bottom side",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.current_transformer.text_9": "100A",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.diodes.header": "Controlling the direction of current",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.diodes.text_1": "Diodes can be used to control the direction of current",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.diodes.text_2": "Diodes will allow current to flow, if the anode is connected to the higher potential ...",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.diodes.text_3": "... and the cathode is connected to the lower potential",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.diodes.text_4": "That's called Forward Bias",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.diodes.text_5": "Otherwise, the diode blocks current flow",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.diodes.text_6": "That's called Reverse Bias",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.electric_train_sounds.header": "Changing the electric train sound",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.electric_train_sounds.text_1": "Electric trains emit a different sound when powered",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.electric_train_sounds.text_2": "Attaching certain blocks can change this sound to a different style",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.energy_meter.header": "Using energy meters",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.energy_meter.text_1": "Energy meters can be used to measure used energy",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.energy_meter.text_2": "Connect the positive feed to the 'feed' node",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.energy_meter.text_3": "Connect the positive load to the 'load' node",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.energy_meter.text_4": "Finally, connect the return through the 'neutral' node",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.energy_meter.text_5": "The meter will start counting energy that flowed through it",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.header": "Ammeters & Voltmeters",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.text_1": "To measure the properties of an electric circuit, use voltmeters and ammeters",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.text_2": "An ammeter measures current flow",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.text_3": "It is connected in series",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.text_4": "This means it is placed along the wire. Notice how it oversees the flow of current",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.text_5": "0.3A",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.text_6": "A voltmeter measures the voltage difference",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.text_7": "It is connected in parallel to the circuit",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.gauges.text_8": "This means it is placed between the two wires. Notice how it probes the points and measures the voltage",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.grounding.header": "The ground as a conductor of electricity",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.grounding.text_1": "The ground can actually conduct electricity.",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.hv_switch.header": "Setting up a High Voltage Switch",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.hv_switch.text_1": "High Voltage Switches can be used to connect or disconnect high voltage circuits",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.hv_switch.text_2": "To create one, place a Connector in the direction of the High Voltage Switch",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.hv_switch.text_3": "Leave a one-block gap between them",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.hv_switch.text_4": "The High Voltage Switch can be operated manually...",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.hv_switch.text_5": "...or with the help of Redstone",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.header": "Electrifying Trains",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.text_1": "Catenary Holders will automatically connect to nearby pole-like blocks",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.text_2": "A catenary system can be used to power trains",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.text_3": "A train, that uses electricity, must have a pantograph that touches the catenary wires ...",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.text_4": "and an Electric Motor ...",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.text_5": "To power the Catenary System, connect the overhead lines to the positive terminal",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.text_6": "Connect the negative to a Ground Rod",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.text_7": "2500 V",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.railway_electrification.text_8": "Pantographs can be dyed",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.relay.header": "Using a relay",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.relay.text_1": "Relays are just switches that can are operated with a small electric current",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.relay.text_2": "Connect the controlling circuit to the 'coil' connectors",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.relay.text_3": "Connect the switched circuit to the remaining connectors",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.relay.text_4": "Wrench the relay to change its state to Normally-Closed (NC)",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.resistance.header": "Effect of a Resistor on a Circuit",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.resistance.text_1": "Without a resistor, the bulb shines at full intensity",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.resistance.text_2": "1kΩ",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.resistance.text_3": "Notice how the bulb is dimmer",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.resistance.text_4": "The resistor is limiting the current flowing through the bulb",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.resistance.text_5": "The downside is, some power is wasted as heat",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.shared.ratio1over2": "1 / 2",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.shared.ratio1over3": "1 / 3",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.shared.ratio3over1": "3 / 1",
  "electroenergetics.ponder.shared.turns10": "10 turns",
